contents.desc: We will keep fighting everyday. EDIT: This video has brought a huge amount of anger, sadness and confusion. And I'm very glad it did. This is how we change the world and have a real conversation on what's wrong with our society.  It's also portant to know for every terrible person, there is at least 5 wonderful people . In this video we are showing you the dark side of society. This is not an issue with our country, as there are 3 different countries in this video.  This is 1 year worth of incidents. The videos are located in the London, Paris and Switzerland.  Our goal is to show you that sadly, there is mistreatment and lack of understanding of disabled people no matter where you go. We WILL keep fighting. For our rights worldwide.   #disability #accessibility #guidedog #assistancedog #servicedog #fyp

stickerText: POV: You live in a society not made for people like you
The problem is you have a dog..
Yeah we going to let you eat, but It's going to be at the back
Excuse me your dog!
Please keep the guide lines clear
What guide lines?
Sorry sorry sorry
Just not infront of the cane love
Stop, no, don't!
Can you remove your dog please
That doesn't mean let him go when my back is turned, it mean leash you dog.
Leave him Clara, he's working üíñ
Pets are not allowed here

"Ignore me I'm working"
Does that mean he never gets cuddles? üò¢
AGHHH WHAT KIND OF DOG IS THAT?
So just a heads up, when he's working that really means he's working, so you cannot touch him
Oh I thought this meant I could...
Driving on a strict  pedestrian area
Step is way too big so I trip
You can go infront "of the car" (on the road)
No it's not safe, he won't let me
Please don't block the exit of the train, thank you

Excuse me, these are the seats for disabled people

Ugh...
